  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "We have an issue open (#5202) in which we'd like to audit and fix our flaky tests. Unfortunately, our current tooling doesn't make this an easy job, as we don't have a good source of historical data on which tests are flaky (failing on one build, then succeeding on another build of the same commit).\r\n\r\nTo get this historical data we'd need to collect all of our stored logs from GitHub Actions and parse them for test failures. It would be much easier to do this however if we made use of a structured data test reporter, and stored off our test reports as build artifacts. \r\n\r\nMost projects make use of the JUnit test report format for this, and there's widely available tooling that supports that data format.\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/marketplace/actions/publish-unit-test-results\r\nhttps://www.npmjs.com/package/mocha-junit-reporter\r\nhttps://www.npmjs.com/package/jest-junit",
